# AES-CBC Padding Oracle

Padding oracle attack against AES-CBC encrypted tokens.

## Description

Exploits improper error handling in AES-CBC decryption to recover
plaintext one byte at a time through padding validation oracles.

## Prerequisites

- Target uses AES-CBC encryption
- Different error messages for valid/invalid padding
- Attacker can modify ciphertext blocks

## Steps

1. Identify padding oracle endpoint
2. Capture valid ciphertext
3. Modify last block byte-by-byte
4. Infer intermediate values from padding errors
